{
  "$comment": [
    "SHARED parity fixtures — the TS<->Python drift gate (eva-validation-function.md §6, step 2).",
    "ONE fixture set, read by BOTH implementations of the EVA readiness contract so neither can",
    "drift silently:",
    "  * Python: functions/evavalidation/tests/test_parity.py feeds each `case`+`evidence` through",
    "    validation.validate_case and asserts `expected` (this runs in THIS function's pytest sweep).",
    "  * TypeScript (wired into verify-all at the M2.B activation, per the plan): a vitest runner feeds",
    "    the SAME fixtures through case-status.ts statusForReviewCase / image-rules.ts evaluateEvaImageRules",
    "    (the Code App computeReadiness() path) and asserts the SAME `expected`.",
    "Fixtures are authored in the canonical TS/Code-App CONTRACT shape (camelCase keys, STRING enums:",
    "imageRole 'overview'|'damage_closeup'|'additional', reviewState 'needs_review'|'conflict'|...);",
    "validation.py accepts these directly, and a vitest runner maps them onto ImageRuleEvidence /",
    "ReviewableField without transformation. The `dataverseShape` fixtures additionally prove the raw",
    "cr1bd_* row shape (what the flow passes un-remapped) yields the identical verdict.",
    "`expected.derivedStatus` applies the load-bearing guard PRECEDENCE from case-status.ts",
    "(terminal-lock is upstream of this Function): missing_required_fields > missing_images >",
    "needs_review > ready_for_eva. `openIssueKinds` is the unordered SET of issue categories",
    "{ missing_field, image_min_count, image_missing_overview, image_missing_closeup, needs_review }",
    "that validate_case must surface in openIssues — order is asserted separately in test_validation.py.",
    "The required-field set is the 7 `required:true` keys in eva-export.ts EVA_FIELD_ORDER:",
    "work_provider, vehicle_model, claimant_name, date_of_loss, date_of_instruction,",
    "accident_circumstances, inspection_address. The other 5 are optional and never gate readiness."
  ],
